Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with source-channel coding and distortion, which are core topics in information theory. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper addresses the problem of energy allocation and management in cyber-physical systems, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses radio communication and time-division scheduling strategies, which are topics related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper considers a system with multiple sensors and derives scheduling strategies, which are topics related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with source compression and distortion, which are topics related to multimedia.
